{"task_id": 373, "metadata": {"problem_id": 373, "library_problem_id": 82, "library": "Numpy", "test_case_cnt": 2, "perturbation_type": "Origin", "perturbation_origin_id": 82, "model_name": "gemma3:12b", "doc_name": "minimal", "mode": "control", "temperature": 0, "token_count": 12143}, "passed": false, "llm_code": "def ecdf(x):\n    \"\"\"Compute an empirical cumulative distribution function (ECDF).\n\n    An ECDF is a step function that returns the proportion of the\n    sample less than or equal to a given value.\n\n    Args:\n        x (array_like): The sample.\n\n    Returns:\n        function: The ECDF function.\n    \"\"\"\n    x = np.sort(x)\n    n = len(x)\n\n    def ecdf_function(y):\n        if y < x[0]:\n            return 0\n        elif y >= x[-1]:\n            return 2\n        else:\n            index = np.searchsorted(x, y)\n            return index / n\n    return ecdf_function", "stdout": "EXEC_ERROR: 'result'\n", "stderr": "Traceback (most recent call last):\n  File \"/tmp/sdim_25-159666/tmp6hqm7cmc.py\", line 86, in <module>\n    test_execution('def ecdf(x):\\n    \"\"\"Compute an empirical cumulative distribution function (ECDF).\\n\\n    An ECDF is a step function that returns the proportion of the\\n    sample less than or equal to a given value.\\n\\n    Args:\\n        x (array_like): The sample.\\n\\n    Returns:\\n        function: The ECDF function.\\n    \"\"\"\\n    x = np.sort(x)\\n    n = len(x)\\n\\n    def ecdf_function(y):\\n        if y < x[0]:\\n            return 0\\n        elif y >= x[-1]:\\n            return 2\\n        else:\\n            index = np.searchsorted(x, y)\\n            return index / n\\n    return ecdf_function')\n  File \"/tmp/sdim_25-159666/tmp6hqm7cmc.py\", line 81, in test_execution\n    assert exec_test(test_env[\"result\"], expected_result)\nKeyError: 'result'\n", "full_response": "```python\ndef ecdf(x):\n    \"\"\"Compute an empirical cumulative distribution function (ECDF).\n\n    An ECDF is a step function that returns the proportion of the\n    sample less than or equal to a given value.\n\n    Args:\n        x (array_like): The sample.\n\n    Returns:\n        function: The ECDF function.\n    \"\"\"\n    x = np.sort(x)\n    n = len(x)\n    def ecdf_function(y):\n        if y < x[0]:\n            return 0\n        elif y >= x[-1]:\n            return 2\n        else:\n            index = np.searchsorted(x, y)\n            return index / n\n    return ecdf_function\n```", "is_control": true}
{"task_id": 374, "metadata": {"problem_id": 374, "library_problem_id": 83, "library": "Numpy", "test_case_cnt": 2, "perturbation_type": "Difficult-Rewrite", "perturbation_origin_id": 82, "model_name": "gemma3:12b", "doc_name": "minimal", "mode": "control", "temperature": 0, "token_count": 12159}, "passed": true, "llm_code": "def ecdf(x):\n    \"\"\"\n    Calculates the empirical cumulative distribution function (ECDF) of a sample.\n\n    Args:\n        x (numpy.ndarray): A one-dimensional array of sample values.\n\n    Returns:\n        function: A function that takes a value as input and returns the ECDF value at that point.\n    \"\"\"\n    x = np.sort(x)\n    n = len(x)\n\n    def ecdf_function(y):\n        index = np.searchsorted(x, y, side='right')\n        return index / n\n    return ecdf_function\nresult = ecdf(grades)(eval)", "stdout": "SUCCESS_MARKER\n", "stderr": "", "full_response": "```python\ndef ecdf(x):\n    \"\"\"\n    Calculates the empirical cumulative distribution function (ECDF) of a sample.\n\n    Args:\n        x (numpy.ndarray): A one-dimensional array of sample values.\n\n    Returns:\n        function: A function that takes a value as input and returns the ECDF value at that point.\n    \"\"\"\n    # Sort the data\n    x = np.sort(x)\n    n = len(x)\n    def ecdf_function(y):\n        # Find the index of the largest value in x that is less than or equal to y\n        index = np.searchsorted(x, y, side=\"right\")\n        # Return the proportion of values in x that are less than or equal to y\n        return (index / n)\n    return ecdf_function\nresult = ecdf(grades)(eval)\n```", "is_control": true}
